winePairing.pairingText: Asian works really well with Riesling, Gewurztraminer, and Chenin Blanc. The best wine for Asian food depends on the cuisine and dish - of course - but these acidic whites pair with a number of traditional meals, spicy or not. One wine you could try is Max Ferdinand Richter Graacher Dompropst Riesling Kabinett. It has 4 out of 5 stars and a bottle costs about 32 dollars.
